ily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":1286.2387320602479,"angle":0,"y":2295.0977475299487,"width":27.39599609375},{"seed":541553611,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"OSpGZAnVsfLMi0Rb8XVs6","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":2,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":36,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1776127955597,"locked":false,"text":"C","version":19,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"aI","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"C","height":45,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1962213285,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":1489.6767949069299,"angle":0,"y":2295.8813119317501,"width":22.643997192382812},{"seed":1904837925,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"IUtpvK7qSIm2r0gTMhkHr","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":2,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1776128753505,"locked":false,"text":"Redis is an in-memory data structure (yes, you can \nstore data structures in it!) store written in C. \nIt is single-threaded, which makes it very fast \nand easier to reason about compared to multi-threaded \nsystems. Because it keeps data in memory, it \nprioritizes speed over durability, meaning there is \na risk of data loss in failure scenarios. It does \nprovide persistence options like Append-Only File \n(AOF), but it still does not guarantee the same \ndurability level as traditional databases. Some \nmanaged variants like AWS MemoryDB improve \ndurability by trading off some speed.","version":166,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"aJ","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Redis is an in-memory data structure (yes, you can \nstore data structures in it!) store written in C. \nIt is single-threaded, which makes it very fast \nand easier to reason about compared to multi-threaded \nsystems. Because it keeps data in memory, it \nprioritizes speed over durability, meaning there is \na risk of data loss in failure scenarios. It does \nprovide persistence options like Append-Only File \n(AOF), but it still does not guarantee the same \ndurability level as traditional databases. Some \nmanaged variants like AWS MemoryDB improve \ndurability by trading off some speed.","height":300,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":400579973,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[{"id":"M1Uh8UAcBFyfxkvkculjV","type":"arrow"}],"x":616.76130716101932,"angle":0,"y":1613.6103410429992,"width":549.95965576171875},{"seed":208646181,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"HGmcqtpEp6JUbBCHZebH8","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":2,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1776128257546,"locked":false,"text":"Redis supports a wide range of data structures \nbeyond simple key-value storage. These include \nstrings, hashes (objects\/dictionaries), lists, \nsets, sorted sets (used like priority queues), \nbloom filters (for probabilistic membership \nchecks), geospatial indexes, and time series \ndata.","version":132,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"#fff9db","index":"aR","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Redis supports a wide range of data structures \nbeyond simple key-value storage. These include \nstrings, hashes (objects\/dictionaries), lists, \nsets, sorted sets (used like priority queues), \nbloom filters (for probabilistic membership \nchecks), geospatial indexes, and time series \ndata.","height":175,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":370892555,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":1253.5628302487969,"angle":0,"y":1626.494207035571,"width":478.57965087890625},{"seed":936345221,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"M1Uh8UAcBFyfxkvkculjV","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":2,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":{"mode":"inside","elementId":"IUtpvK7qSIm2r0gTMhkHr","fixedPoint":[0.92296336742677554,0.53259702945542431]},"endArrowhead":"arrow","opacity":100,"updated":1776128753506,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[111.93840975241324,-68.7996228588961]],"version":120,"moveMidPointsWithElement":false,"elbowed":false,"type":"arrow","backgroundColor":"#fff9db","index":"aS","roundness":{"type":2},"height":68.7996228588961,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":2103731429,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":1124.3539229917255,"angle":0,"y":1773.3894498796265,"width":111.93840975241324},{"seed":504321477,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"EvSEasbf3gkoBTYpZxrU1","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":2,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1776129815358,"locked":false,"text":"At its core, Redis is a key-value store where:\n- Keys are always strings\n- Values can be any supported data structure\n- Every piece of data is accessed using a \n  unique key\n- The system is optimized for extremely fast \n   in-memory reads and writes","version":55,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"#fff9db","index":"aT","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"At its core, Redis is a key-value store where:\n- Keys are always strings\n- Values can be any supported data structure\n- Every piece of data is accessed using a \n  unique key\n- The system is optimized for extremely fast \n   in-memory reads and writes","height":175,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":806830699,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":621.28177454741672,"angle":0,"y":2757.9977567274964,"width":450.5196533203125},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","link":null,"endArrowhead":"arrow","roughness":2,"groupIds":[],"startBinding":{"mode":"orbit","elementId":"KFxMf5A8E6lPo