752,"seed":119069733,"boundElements":[],"y":4038.9853131498953,"opacity":100,"height":2.9280619384685451,"points":[[0,0],[539.48643824269175,2.9280619384685451]],"width":539.48643824269175,"frameId":null,"polygon":false,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":1532072907},{"seed":1296369509,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"VI_UBv6u7INvXOoxg--oC","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":2,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1776140902748,"locked":false,"text":"Redis can be used as a distributed lock to\nmaintain consistency when multiple processes\ntry to update the same data at the same time.\nThis is useful in systems like ticket booking or\npreventing duplicate actions.","version":433,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"#ffec99","index":"b1A","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Redis can be used as a distributed lock to\nmaintain consistency when multiple processes\ntry to update the same data at the same time.\nThis is useful in systems like ticket booking or\npreventing duplicate actions.","height":125,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1663230571,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[{"id":"2mMbj2EMlyKsXhGKV_inf","type":"arrow"}],"x":658.06527050680347,"angle":0,"y":4103.8938623706927,"width":465.31976318359375},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","link":null,"roughness":2,"groupIds":[],"index":"b1FV","backgroundColor":"#ebfbee","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"version":817,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1776140902748,"id":"vF1VeCMh_GDjLeWQrAK9I","x":1430.2476047310245,"seed":1882823141,"boundElements":[],"y":4272.4630695306678,"opacity":100,"height":29.306040839483117,"width":53.488205326739823,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":219241739},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","link":null,"roughness":2,"groupIds":[],"index":"b1Fl","backgroundColor":"#ffec99","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"version":527,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1776140902748,"id":"F1gofyFAky6iq3OETyovB","x":1297.807582929617,"seed":1920117739,"boundElements":[],"y":4350.1430535441887,"opacity":100,"height":24.56446967318243,"width":52.403478314432505,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":1956086699},{"seed":543665157,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"Ewe1wMonXDUkJ2xGNsDdd","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":2,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1776140902748,"locked":false,"text":"A simple lock can be implemented using atomic\noperations like INCR with a TTL. The first\nprocess to get value 1 acquires the lock, while\nothers wait and retry. Once done, the lock is\nreleased using DEL so others can proceed.","version":453,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"#ffec99","index":"b1G","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"A simple lock can be implemented using atomic\noperations like INCR with a TTL. The first\nprocess to get value 1 acquires the lock, while\nothers wait and retry. Once done, the lock is\nreleased using DEL so others can proceed.","height":125,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1642059339,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[{"id":"2mMbj2EMlyKsXhGKV_inf","type":"arrow"},{"id":"tg4ptyStoqz84nasCSwNm","type":"arrow"}],"x":1160.3783356325514,"angle":0,"y":4249.942042004106,"width":448.13970947265625},{"seed":2081474149,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"MrS_8dSsxgR-mwJWrF9tj","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":2,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1776140902748,"locked":false,"text":"However, distributed locks add complexity, and\nmany systems already provide consistency at the\ndatabase level. For stronger guarantees,\nadvanced solutions like Redlock with fencing\ntokens ca